<br>
Lasgalen doesn't seek to find how he's &quot;unique&quot; or &quot;different&quot; from other druids or Fier'Dal.  In fact, he aspires to be as &quot;druidly&quot; as he can be.  His dilemma is in figuring out how to do that.  How does one articulate activist &quot;true neutrality&quot;?  I know Kimaya and I each have our own opinions on the matter, and our opinions are very different, and yet they both fall under the umbrella quite well.<br>
<br>
Also, I'm not telling anyone how they have to play their characters.  I'm just saying what I would do if I were to play a High Elf. <p><center><img src="http://home.earthlink.net/~andersonrob/lasgalensig.jpg" border="0"></center>
